commit.message:
Fix #595: Unbreak clisp which doesn't use :spawn comm style

The default value for SLYNK-MREPL::*DEDICATED-OUTPUT-STREAM-BUFFERING* depends on
the comm style and, previously, a rare but possible 'nil' comm style (as in Clisp)
would also prevent a gray stream from being used for the dedicated output stream,

So a native stream would be used instead.  This is possible, but only
on sbcl and cmucl.  So always make a gray stream, regardless of the
value of SLYNK-MREPL::*DEDICATED-OUTPUT-STREAM-BUFFERING*.

Fix #595, Fix #600.

* contrib/slynk-mrepl.lisp (open-dedicated-output-stream): Always
use line-buffering for the dedicated output stream.

Per #596: Robustify INT signal handling for Lispworks

* slynk/backend/lispworks.lisp (set-sigint-handler)
(install-sigint-handler): Use SYS::UNIX-SIGINT.

Per #596: Activate package-local nicknames for Lispworks

* slynk/backend/lispworks.lisp (package-local-nicknames): New impl.

Fix #587: Fix typo in slynk/backend/allegro.lisp

slynk-backend:find-symbo2l -> slynk-backend:find-symbol2

* slynk/backend/allegro.lisp (with-redirected-y-or-n-p): Fix typo.

Fix #594, #595: Unbreak for non-SBCL

Broken in e266e24721db22fddcf8dac53ac3c1618502a47a in an undertested PR.

Reported and fix found by @LdBeth

* slynk/slynk.lisp (generic-method-specs): Don't use sb-mop, use
slynk-mop instead.

Don't accidentally concatenate symbols in sly-package-fu--insert-symbol

Related to #560.

* contrib/sly-package-fu.el (sly-package-fu--insert-symbol): Fix.

Improve form-parsing heuristics of 'sly-import-symbol-at-point'

Previously, if a DEFPACKAGE form had no :USE or :IMPORT-FROM subforms
at, C-c i would not be able to find a suitable palce for a new
:IMPORT-FROM subform.  This commit fixes that.

Related to #560

* contrib/sly-package-fu.el
(sly-package-fu--create-new-import-from): Fix finding suitable
place for new :import-from.

Fix #560: Correctly find :IMPORT-FROM for packages with `.` in name

For example, if the package is `bknr.datastore`, it'll keep creating
multiple `(:import-from ...)` statements.

* contrib/sly-package-fu.el (sly-package-fu--search-import-from):
Don't regexp-quote twice.

Per #560: Adjust new tests for sly-package-fu.el

Instead of strings, use lisp forms, which are easier to read.  Make
some tests where :USE subforms aren't present.  Use
find-file-noselect.  Change name of test.

test/sly-package-fu-tests.el (package-fu-import): Rework.

Per #560: Add basic tests for contrib/sly-package-fu.el

* test/sly-package-fu-tests.el: New file.

Unbreak define-sly-ert-test when used M-x compile-defun

* lib/sly-tests.el (sly-tests-auto-tags): Protect against
file-less compilation.

Fix test/sly-fontifying-fu-tests.el

More than one face may be applied to a region, and the test didn't
expect that.

* test/sly-fontifying-fu-tests.el (font-lock-magic): Fix.

Per #588, #586: Advertise new M-x sly-remove-method

* NEWS.md: mention sly-remove-method

* doc/sly.texi: mention sly-remove-method

Add top-level .dir-locals.el

This sets the variable elisp-flymake-byte-compile-load-path which
allows flymake-mode to work properly in the lib/*.el files.

* .dir-locals.el: New file.

Per #588: Adjust logic around M-x sly-remove-method

* sly.el (sly-remove-method): Use sly-eval.

* lib/sly-completion.el (sly-parse): Require it.
(sly--read-method): Rework.  Add docstring.  Fix CL terminology.

* slynk/slynk.lisp (remove-method-by-name): Rename from
undefine-method.  Just error when method not found.  Add docstring
(generic-method-specs): Rename from method-selectors.  Add
docstring.
Add sly-remove-method

Fix #581: Reset output stream column when flushing listener streams

Close #583.

Streams, whether gray or not, have a so-called output-column or
line-column.  This change makes sure to reset it to 0 when the stream
is flushed, fixing the REPL problems described in #581.

In slynk/slynk-gray.lisp a new generic RESET-STREAM-LINE-COLUMN is
added, with a method for SLY's gray stream couple class,
SLY-OUTPUT-STREAM, and a couple of extra methods for SBCL and CMUCL,
which aren't always using gray streams in the context where
stream-flushing is needed.

This allows us to call RESET-STREAM-LINE-COLUMN safely in
slynk/slynk.lisp's FLUSH-LISTENER-STREAMS (except for abcl, which has
some problem I didn't investigate).

* slynk/slynk-gray.lisp (reset-stream-line-column): New generic and
  methods.

* slynk/slynk.lisp (flush-listener-streams): Call
  reset-stream-line-column.

commit.message:
Per #564: Add SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2 for ad-hoc symbol-finding needs

Slynk backends use a decent amount of ad-hoc symbol finding.  This is
due to some backend files, which are READ before slynk.lisp (and the
SLYNK package is defined is loaded occasionally need to check things
in the Slynk packge (at run-time, of course).

This is a common source of problem, so its a good idea to do all this
symbol-finding behind an abstraction, which is the new
SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2.  Currently the implementation of that
sucks, but maybe that can be fixed later.

* slynk/slynk-backend.lisp: New SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2.
* slynk/backend/abcl.lisp: Use SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2.
* slynk/backend/allegro.lisp: Use SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2.
* slynk/backend/clasp.lisp: Use SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2.
* slynk/backend/lispworks.lisp: Use SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2.
* slynk/backend/mkcl.lisp: Use SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2.
* slynk/slynk-apropos.lisp: Use SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2.
* slynk/slynk-source-path-parser.lisp: Use SLYNK-BACKEND:FIND-SYMBOL2.

Fix #564: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX for reading symbol names

SLY commands stopped working when using named-readtables and :PRESERVE
case. Internal parts of SLYNK would start looking for symbols with
lowercase symbol-names, which is nonsensical.

Add robustness to symbol lookups of the form:

    (read-from-string "a-package::a-symbol")

by giving them stable reader settings:

    (with-standard-io-syntax ...)

so that they work the same independent of the reader settings in the
image.

* slynk/backend/abcl.lisp: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX.
* slynk/backend/allegro.lisp: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX.
* slynk/backend/clasp.lisp: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX.
* slynk/backend/lispworks.lisp: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX.
* slynk/backend/mkcl.lisp: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX.
* slynk/slynk-apropos.lisp: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX.
* slynk/slynk-backend.lisp: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX.
* slynk/slynk-source-path-parser.lisp: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX.
* slynk/slynk.asd: Use WITH-STANDARD-IO-SYNTAX.

Co-authored-by: João Távora <joaotavora@gmail.com>
